Class Order

java.lang.Object
Order
public class Order extends Object
Creates an Order Object that stores details about an order

This class is responsible for storing details about an order such as the date and time it was ordered, the customer who ordered it, and the list of drinks of in an order.

Associated FXML file: iceBlendedController.fxml

  • Constructor Details

    • Order

      public Order(int customerID, double totalPrice)
      Constructs a new Order object with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      customerID - used to associate each order with a specific customer
      totalPrice - the total price of the order including tax. This method will also set the Order Objects month, week, date, hour, year, and combineDate variables by using the LocalDateTime function to get the current time when the object is created. It will then parse through this data to properly assign each parssed data to its respective variable. This function will also call dbManager, so that the information of the order can be inserted into the database.

    • Order

      public Order(int orderID, int customerID, double totalPrice, int month, int week, int date, int hour, int year, String combineDate)
      Constructs a new Order object given the specified details.
      Parameters:
      orderID - each order has a specific id associcated with it
      customerID - used to associate each order with a specific customer
      totalPrice - the total price of the order including tax.
      month - the month in which the order was placed
      week - the week in which the order was placed
      date - the data in which the order was placed
      hour - the hour in which the order was placed
      year - the year in which the order was placed
      combineDate - the full date including the time in which the order was placed.
